# Copilot Instructions — {{.Project}}

> This repo follows the Korva Harness Engineering contract. Copilot
> Chat reads these instructions automatically; the rules below are
> non-negotiable.

## Before any change

1. Run `./init.sh`. Every line must be `[OK]`. If anything is `[FAIL]`,
   stop and surface it — do not proceed.
2. Read `progress/current.md`. A session may already be in flight;
   continue it rather than starting fresh.
3. Open `feature_list.json` and locate the `in_progress` row. If none,
   pick the lowest-id `pending` row via `korva harness next`.

## Hard rules

- **One feature at a time.** The state machine enforces it; don't
  work around the constraint.
- **`done` requires green tests.** `./init.sh` must end `[OK]` after
  your changes before marking anything `done`.
- **Document while you work** in `progress/current.md`, not at the
  end.
- **Read `docs/*`** (architecture, conventions, verification) before
  inventing patterns.

## State machine commands

```
korva harness next            # next pending feature
korva harness start <id>      # pending → in_progress
korva harness done <id>       # in_progress → done
korva harness block <id>      # mark blocked
korva harness status          # counts + current feature
```

The same verbs are reachable through MCP as `vault_harness_*` tools
when the Korva Vault is running.

## Closing a session

1. `./init.sh` exits `0`.
2. Move the session entry from `progress/current.md` to
   `progress/history.md`; reset `progress/current.md` to its
   template.
3. `korva harness done <id>`.

## When stuck

Write the blocker into `progress/current.md`, run
`korva harness block <id>`, and stop. Do not invent workarounds, do
not edit `init.sh` to mask the failure, do not bypass the state
machine by editing `feature_list.json` by hand.
